-> iostat:
----------
    
    -> The iostat command in Linux is used to monitor CPU usage and disk I/O (Input/Output) statistics. It helps system administrators analyze system performance, disk activity, and device load.

    -> The command is part of the sysstat package.

    -> Syntax:

        # iostat [option(s)]
    
    -> Installing iostat command:

        # apt install sysstat (Ubuntu/ Debian)

        # yum/dnf install sysstat (RHEL, CentOS)

    -> Continuous monitoring:

        # iostat 2 //Display the output every 2 seconds continuosly.

        # iostat 2 10 //Display the output every 2 seconds for only 10 times.

    -> Display only the CPU info:

        # iostat -c 1 5

    -> Display only the Disk info:

        # iostat -d 1 5

    -> Monitor a specific  device:

        # iostat -x sda

-> Use Cases:

    -> Detect disk bottlenecks
    -> Troubleshoot slow systems
    -> Analyze storage performance
    -> Monitor server workload
    -> Check high I/O wait issues
